A mail room at the CPUT's Cape Town campus has been damaged in a petrol bomb attack. CAPE TOWN - A mail room at the Cape Peninsula University of Technology (CPUT)'s Cape Town campus has been damaged in a petrol bomb attack.The building on the Cape Town campus was targeted on Monday.After more than a month's break, most staff members are expected to return to work today.Students and workers were forced to vacate campuses, amid the Fees Must Fall protests.End-of-year exams are scheduled to begin next week Monday.The university's Lauren Kansley says, The fire affected the mail and firefighters were on scene. The matter is still being investigated. LISTEN: CPUT entrance petrol bombed leaving exams postponed by a week(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)